Providence Hall High School
September 9 at 2:39 PM ·

Parents and Students:
Thanks to a USDA free meal waiver, Providence Hall Charter School will begin offering meals at no cost to all enrolled students beginning Thursday, Sept 10th at all locations. No students will be charged for breakfast or lunch through the month of December.

All schools will serve free meals in the school cafeteria. Online or Flex students will be able to continue to order meals a week in advance and pick-up accordingly at your students' school location.

For any additional questions, please reach out to our Food Service Director, Mapu Weiss, at mweiss@providencehall.com

post_text:
Have you dreamed of what opportunities will benefit your child’s future?

What sort of middle and high school foundation is needed?

Do you imagine a fully accredited International Baccalaureate program that will prepare your child for the global economy?

Have you visualized a school with concurrent enrollment, Career Technical Ed, IB classes, and Advanced Placement offerings?

Can you see your child excited to choose from band, orchestra, choir, guitar, theater, and sports?

Excellence and success start with being given opportunities and support.

Give your student the chance to excel in the classroom as well as to make the most of their talents.

Providence Hall provides that supportive, small-school environment, along with extracurricular opportunities to build towards the future.

Student success and opportunity are central to Providence Hall Charter School.

Dear Providence Hall Junior High Community...
I am so grateful for the opportunity to get to be your principal next year.
We have a fantastic team in place, and we are all counting down the days until we get to see your faces again!!!
Please don’t hesitate to reach out with any questions, concerns, compliments, and/or chocolate. ❤️
This is going to be a new chapter for Providence Hall, but it has hope, happiness, and opportunity for growth written all over it!
Thank you to Brian Fauver and Odette Desmarais for all of the love and dedication you have given over the years!
See you in a few short weeks.

...to help your child find their place in a diverse, inclusive, international community.

Open your child’s backpack and discover a lifelong love of learning...

...with the IB World School Program at Providence Hall Charter School.

At Providence Hall Charter School, understanding your child is vital.

That’s why your student will be in a small class.

Low student numbers allow teachers to know your child personally.

Teachers can then guide your student to the activities that are just right for them.

Your child will follow their own unique path of development.

Our individualized environment and learning tools empower your child to progressively challenge their own abilities.

This allows them to achieve more than you ever thought possible.

Discover the benefits of significantly more individual attention at Providence Hall Charter School.

Providence Hall will be offering summer high school baseball through the Murray High School summer baseball league. Deadline for signing up will be May 25th. SIGN UP USING THE LINK BELOW.
Once we know the number of players we will let you know what the cost is per player. Games start June 2 (the only Saturday game) and run through the month of June and first 2 weeks in July. They play every Monday and Wed and alternate on Fridays. Its a total of 14 games and a tournament. Cost will be dependent on the number of players. For more information contact Mr Marshall at nmarshall@providencehall.com

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScBLefKlJ50ilDYe61nzBM5YaYIK6P2eGxxAdNO2-eU9y5wyw/viewform

Parents and students
Over the weekend the police were searching for an armed suspect near Blackridge Reservoir. The police instituted a shelter-in-place on Saturday as they looked for the suspect but have since lifted the advisement. You can find out more information on the progress of Unified Police by visiting the Herriman facebook page:

https://www.facebook.com/pg/HerrimanCity/posts/?ref=page_internal

Our schools will resume as normal on Monday and will continue to work with UPD to monitor the progress of this investigation.

Providence Hall is the only fully accredited International Baccalaureate school grades K-12 in Utah. There are three campuses; elementary K-5, junior high 6-8, and high school 9-12.
Providence Hall's open enrollment for 2018-19 will begin Jan 1st and run through Feb 13th, 2018. For news students interested in enrolling, please go to our website after January 1st and click on the enrollment tab:
